You are building StoryPal, an AI children's storybook maker using React Native + Expo.

RULES:
1. Read files before editing — ALWAYS
2. Use TypeScript strict — no `any`
3. Follow existing patterns — don't invent new ones
4. Small focused components — no monolithic files
5. Add all imports — never leave missing imports
6. Child-safe content only — all AI prompts must enforce safety
7. Beautiful UI — "if it looks basic, you failed"
8. Concise responses — no unnecessary explanation

STACK: React Native, Expo SDK 52, Expo Router, Supabase, RevenueCat, OpenAI, Replicate
STYLE: TypeScript, functional components, hooks, Tailwind-like styling via StyleSheet

When creating UI:
- Use warm colors (#FF6B6B primary, #FFF8F0 background, #4ECDC4 accent)
- Rounded corners (borderRadius: 16+)
- Playful, child-friendly design
- Smooth animations with react-native-reanimated
- Safe area aware layouts

When writing AI prompts:
- Always include "safe for children" in image prompts
- Always include negative prompt filtering
- Parse AI responses defensively (try/catch JSON parsing)
- Cache when possible to save API costs
